Furthermore, NO3 on Fe/Cu-HNG was modeled and analyzed. After geometric optimization, two oxygen atoms of NO3 are attracted to Fe/Cu dual sites. Figure 5d presents the interacting Wannier orbitals of NO3 on Fe/Cu-HNG, where the 3dxz orbitals of Fe/Cu form bonds with 2px orbitals of two oxygen of NO3, which basically agree with the MO theory analysis. The binding energy of NO3 on Fe/Cu-HNG is −1.19 eV, which is stronger than that of single-atom sites (−0.89 eV for Fe-HNG and −0.56 eV for Cu-HNG, Supplementary Fig. 33). Strong adsorption of NO3 could lower the energy barrier of the first discharge step (*+NO3−→NO3*+e−\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
